        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 4:45PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 443 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a pair of slow-moving
thunderstorms near Vinton, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could cause minor tree limb damage and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vinton, Urbana, Vinton Memorial Airport, Benton County Fairgrounds,
Rodgers Park, Wildcat Bluff Park, Benton City Park, Cheney, and
Hoefle-Dulin Park.

This includes Interstate 380 between mile markers 40 and 48.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring and may lead to localized flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways. Stay away from
flooded areas. Report any flooding to local law enforcement.</instruction>
